  "prompt": "What is the meaning of Urdu compound word \u201cghairat-e-ashiq\u201d?",
  "response": "The Urdu compound word \"ghairat-e-ashiq\" can be broken down into two parts: \"ghairat\" and \"ashiq.\" \n\n- \"Ghairat\" generally means honor, self-respect, or pride.\n- \"Ashiq\" means lover.\n\nPutting them together, \"ghairat-e-ashiq\" refers to the sense of honor, pride, or self-respect associated with a lover. It could denote the lover's concern for maintaining respect or dignity in the context of love or romance. This term often touches on the emotional and cultural nuances of honor in relationships.",
